  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>For all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k]]></fr:tex>, the filtration <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^k(K_\mathbb {C})\simeq \operatorname {H}^k(K_A)\otimes \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> defines a Hodge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-structure of weight <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n+k]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^k(K_A)]]></fr:tex>, i.e. the filtration <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(n+k)]]></fr:tex>-opposite to its complex conjugate (which makes sense, since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\subset \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>).</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:backmatter>
    <fr:tree toc="false" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
